# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# caps/seed — FROZEN low-level capability ground truth
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# This file is FROZEN. Do not add new entries here.
# It contains ONLY true low-level functions whose capabilities cannot
# be inferred from the callgraph:
#   - Panicking intrinsics (no body to analyze)
#   - Raw allocation (unsafe, below the abstraction layer)
#   - Runtime bootstrap / IO internals (compiler-generated)
#   - libc FFI syscalls (leaf nodes with no Rust body)
#   - Process/environment functions (opaque to the callgraph)
#   - Spawn functions (unstructured concurrency — "concurrency goto")
#   - Rustc driver/lint (our own toolchain)
#   - Unwind/libunwind FFI (no Rust body)
#
# For corrections to std functions whose inferred caps are wrong,
# use caps/suppress instead.
#
# Loading order: std -> deps -> seed -> suppress -> ext
# Later files override earlier ones. Entries with caps "freeze" a
# function — propagation does NOT add to them.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

